      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>George Sawyer was a prominent minister in the Methodist Episcopal Church in New York State.  His son Azariah H. 
	  Sawyer became a judge.  The relationship of George Sawyer to John Sawyer is uncertain.  The items relating to John are dated 
	  earlier; George's father's name was Manasseh so perhaps John was an elder brother or other relative.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">John and George Sawyer Papers</emph> consists of correspondence and a number of authorizations,  
		 in the names of each man, to preach in the Methodist Episcopal Church.  There are also a few miscellaneous other items, such 
		 as a subscription form for a seminary.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
